# E-commerce Back End
 
## Description
 
This project is the back end for an e-commerce site, built with a working Express.js API configured to use Sequelize to interact with a PostgreSQL database. It demonstrates the fundamental architecture of online retail platforms by modeling categories, products, and tags — and the relationships between them — through an Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) layer.
 
The application exposes a full set of RESTful API routes that allow a user to create, read, update, and delete categories, products, and tags. Each model is connected through Sequelize associations, including a many-to-many relationship between products and tags managed through a join table.
 
